Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the rice. When boiling, stir in the @brown basmati rice{150%g} and cook rapidly for ~{25%minutes}.

> TIP: Add more water if it starts to evaporate too much.

When cooked, drain the rice in a #sieve{} and return to the saucepan, off the heat.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}. Chop the @broccoli{1} into florets (little trees). Cut the @baby corn{60%g} in half.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the @Panang curry paste{25%g} and cook for ~{1%minute} to release the flavour.

Once it has become fragrant, add the @coconut milk{400%ml} and stir. Raise the heat to high, and bring the sauce to the boil.

Once bubbling, reduce the heat back to medium and add the @diced sweet potato{300%g} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Simmer gently on medium heat, ~{15%minutes}.

Add the baby corn and broccoli florets to the frying pan, cover with a #lid{} (or tin foil) and continue to simmer until the veggies are tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> TIP: The corn should have a little bit of a bite left in it when cooked.

Stir half the peanuts into the curry. Taste for seasoning and add a bit more salt if necessary.